<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
  <mtable frame="solid" rowalign="center" groupalign="{ right }" rowlines="solid">
    <mtr>
      <mtd><maligngroup/><mtext>This-is-right-aligned</mtext></mtd>
    </mtr>
    <mtr>
      <mrow>
        <maligngroup/>
        <mo>(</mo>
        <mtable alignmentscope="false true">
	  <mtr>
	    <mtd><mn>1<malignmark edge="right"/></mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	  </mtr>
	  <mtr>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	  </mtr>
	  <mtr>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd>
	    <mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd>
	  </mtr>
	</mtable>
	<mo>)</mo>
      </mrow>
    </mtr>
    <mtr>
      <mtd>
        <mtext color="blue">
	The two cells above contains one alignment group. However, the second cell
	is made of an mrow element and a 3x3 table, with alignment scope disabled
	for the first column, so that a malignmark element has effect on the
	surrounding table.
	</mtext>
      </mtd>
    </mtr>
  </mtable>
</math>
